a0:["$","p","92",{"className":"mb-4 text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed sm:leading-8","children":["Research suggests customers become frustrated after waiting more than 3 minutes in line. The ideal target is under 2 minutes from joining the queue to completing the transaction. However, perceived wait time matters as much as actual time. Engaging customers with displays, samples, or entertainment can make waits feel shorter."]}]
a1:["$","h3","93",{"className":"mb-4 font-bold text-2xl tracking-tighter sm:text-3xl","children":["How much does self-checkout cost for a small retailer?"]}]
a2:["$","p","94",{"className":"mb-4 text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed sm:leading-8","children":["Basic self-checkout solutions range from $1,500 to $5,000 per station for tablet-based systems. Full kiosk setups cost $15,000-$30,000 but are typically overkill for small retailers. Many POS providers now offer self-checkout add-ons to existing systems at lower costs. Factor in ongoing software fees and maintenance."]}]
a3:["$","h3","95",{"className":"mb-4 font-bold text-2xl tracking-tighter sm:text-3xl","children":["Should I eliminate cashiers entirely and go fully self-checkout?"]}]
a4:["$","p","96",{"className":"mb-4 text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed sm:leading-8","children":["No. Research consistently shows that customers value having a choice. Many shoppers, particularly older demographics or those buying complex items, prefer human interaction. The best approach is a hybrid model with both options available. Use self-checkout to handle simple transactions and free up staff for customer service."]}]
a5:["$","h3","97",{"className":"mb-4 font-bold text-2xl tracking-tighter sm:text-3xl","children":["How do I train existing staff to be faster without making them feel criticized?"]}]
a6:["$","p","98",{"className":"mb-4 text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed sm:leading-8","children":["Frame speed training as skill development, not criticism. Celebrate improvements publicly and coach individually. Use gamification like friendly competitions with prizes. Share efficiency tips as team learnings rather than individual corrections. Focus on removing obstacles like unnecessary approvals rather than pressuring for raw speed."]}]
